{"type":"session_message","session_id":"ses_2776e44adffeWi2i79hWf80hqu","role":"assistant","message_id":"msg_d8891fbed001F0PbovrXa1t05S","parts":[{"id":"prt_d889218dd001ejK92uIFb4Le0I","messageID":"msg_d8891fbed001F0PbovrXa1t05S","sessionID":"ses_2776e44adffeWi2i79hWf80hqu","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_67c2148230cf4e729dfed154","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/workspace/atest/run.py","limit":100},"output":"<path>/workspace/atest/run.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: #!/usr/bin/env python3\n2: \n3: \"\"\"A script for running Robot Framework's own acceptance tests.\n4: \n5: Usage:  atest/run.py [-I name] [-S] [-R] [options] [data]\n6: \n7: `data` is path (or paths) of the file or directory under the `atest/robot`\n8: folder to execute. If `data` is not given, all tests except for tests tagged\n9: with `no-ci` are executed.\n10: \n11: Available `options` are in general normal Robot Framework options, but there\n12: are some exceptions listed below.\n13: \n14: By default, the same Python interpreter that is used for running this script is\n15: also used for running tests. That can be changed by using the `--interpreter`\n16: (`-I`) option. It can be the name of the interpreter like `pypy3` or a path to\n17: the selected interpreter like `/usr/bin/python39`. If the interpreter itself\n18: needs arguments, the interpreter and its arguments need to be quoted like\n19: `\"py -3.12\"`.\n20: \n21: To enable schema validation for all suites, use the `--schema-validation`\n22: (`-S`) option. This is the same as setting the `ATEST_VALIDATE_OUTPUT`\n23: environment variable to `TRUE`.\n24: \n25: Use `--rerun-failed (`-R`)` to re-execute failed tests from the previous run.\n26: \n27: The output directory is set based on the interpreter version and operating\n28: system by default. It can be changed using the normal `--outputdir` option.\n29: \n30: Examples:\n31: $ atest/run.py\n32: $ atest/run.py --exclude no-ci atest/robot/standard_libraries\n33: $ atest/run.py --interpreter pypy3\n34: $ atest/run.py --rerun-failed\n35: \n36: The results of the test execution are written into an interpreter specific\n37: directory under the `atest/results` directory. Temporary outputs created\n38: during the execution are created under the system temporary directory.\n39: \"\"\"\n40: \n41: import argparse\n42: import os\n43: import shutil\n44: import signal\n45: import subprocess\n46: import sys\n47: import tempfile\n48: from pathlib import Path\n49: \n50: from interpreter import Interpreter\n51: \n52: CURDIR = Path(__file__).parent\n53: LATEST = str(CURDIR / \"results/{interpreter.output_name}-latest.xml\")\n54: ARGUMENTS = \"\"\"\n55: --doc Robot Framework acceptance tests\n56: --metadata interpreter:{interpreter}\n57: --variable-file {variable_file};{interpreter.path};{interpreter.name};{interpreter.version}\n58: --pythonpath {pythonpath}\n59: --output-dir {output_dir}\n60: --splitlog\n61: --console dotted\n62: --console-width 100\n63: --suite-stat-level 3\n64: --log NONE\n65: --report NONE\n66: \"\"\".strip()\n67: \n68: \n69: def atests(interpreter, arguments, output_dir=None, schema_validation=False):\n70:     output_dir, temp_dir = _get_directories(interpreter, output_dir)\n71:     arguments = list(_get_arguments(interpreter, output_dir)) + list(arguments)\n72:     rc = _run(arguments, temp_dir, interpreter, schema_validation)\n73:     if rc < 251:\n74:         _rebot(rc, output_dir, interpreter)\n75:     return rc\n76: \n77: \n78: def _get_directories(interpreter, output_dir=None):\n79:     name = interpreter.output_name\n80:     if output_dir:\n81:         output_dir = Path(output_dir)\n82:     else:\n83:         output_dir = CURDIR / \"results\" / name\n84:     temp_dir = Path(tempfile.gettempdir()) / \"robotatest\" / name\n85:     if output_dir.exists():\n86:         shutil.rmtree(output_dir)\n87:     if temp_dir.exists():\n88:         shutil.rmtree(temp_dir)\n89:     os.makedirs(temp_dir)\n90:     return output_dir, temp_dir\n91: \n92: \n93: def _get_arguments(interpreter, output_dir):\n94:     arguments = ARGUMENTS.format(\n95:         interpreter=interpreter,\n96:         variable_file=CURDIR / \"interpreter.py\",\n97:         pythonpath=CURDIR / \"resources\",\n98:         output_dir=output_dir,\n99:     )\n100:     for line in arguments.splitlines():\n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 175. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\n\"\"\"A script for running Robot Framework's own acceptance tests.\n\nUsage:  atest/run.py [-I name] [-S] [-R] [options] [data]\n\n`data` is path (or paths) of the file or directory under the `atest/robot`\nfolder to execute. If `data` is not given, all tests except for tests tagged\nwith `no-ci` are executed.\n\nAvailable `options` are in general normal Robot Framework options, but there\nare some exceptions listed below.\n\nBy default, the same Python interpreter that is used for running this script is\nalso used for running tests. That can be changed by using the `--interpreter`\n(`-I`) option. It can be the name of the interpreter like `pypy3` or a path to\nthe selected interpreter like `/usr/bin/python39`. If the interpreter itself\nneeds arguments, the interpreter and its arguments need to be quoted like\n`\"py -3.12\"`.\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"atest/run.py","time":{"start":1776112769950,"end":1776112769955}}}]}
